lctech f1c200s: park spi1 DMA, run the ESP link over PIO

With DMA wired, host->ESP command frames go unanswered while reads
(boot-up event, version) work -- still true after fixing the burst
(INCR4, patch 0015) and the TX beat width (byte, patch 0015 v2); irq
counters show transfers completing mechanically. Root cause needs
bench instrumentation (scope on MOSI, printk in the transaction
engine), not more remote iterations. PIO is proven on this stack
(full scans + the app's SoftAP ran on it), so the dmas wiring comes
out; the DMA controller node, the driver backport and the engine
fixes stay for the bench effort.

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
@@ -73,11 +73,12 @@
 &spi1 {
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
 	pinctrl-0 = <&spi1_pe_pins>;
-	/* NDMA DRQ 0x05 = SPI1 Rx/Tx (F1C200s manual 3.6.7.4); spi-sun6i
-	 * uses the channels automatically and falls back to PIO without. */
-	dmas = <&dma SUN4I_DMA_NORMAL 5>,
-	       <&dma SUN4I_DMA_NORMAL 5>;
-	dma-names = "rx", "tx";
+	/* DMA parked (PIO): with channels wired, host->ESP command frames
+	 * never get answered while reads work -- unresolved after the burst
+	 * (INCR4) and TX-width (byte) fixes; needs bench instrumentation.
+	 * The DMA controller + engine fixes stay in the tree for that work.
+	 * Re-enable by restoring: dmas = <&dma SUN4I_DMA_NORMAL 5> x2 +
+	 * dma-names = "rx", "tx". */
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
